  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Skill",
      "args": {
        "skill": "stm32agent",
        "args": "Tail the VCP output from the target"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 vcp tail --follow",
        "description": "Stream VCP serial output from target until Ctrl-C",
        "timeout": 600000
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "Streaming VCP output with `--follow` \u2014 this will run until you press Ctrl-C.\n**COM9 is held by another process** \u2014 something else (minicom, PuTTY, CubeIDE's serial monitor, etc.) has the port open and denied access.\n\n**To fix:**\n\n1. Close whatever tool is holding **COM9** \u2014 common culprits:\n   - CubeIDE serial monitor (click the red \u25a0 stop button in the Console view)\n   - PuTTY / Tera Term / minicom / screen session\n   - Any previously opened `stm32 vcp` instance still running in another terminal\n\n2. Then re-run the tail \u2014 I'll pick it back up automatically, or just say \"tail VCP again\" and I'll re-invoke.\n\nIf you're not sure what's holding it, you can find the owning process on Windows with:\n```\nGet-Process | Where-Object { $_.MainWindowTitle -match \"COM9\" }\n# or\nhandle64.exe COM9   # if Sysinternals Handle is installed\n```"
}